  "time_ut": 1658218030,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0ddd\u0da0\u0dca\u0da0\u0dd2\u0dba\u0da7 \u0db8\u0d9c\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dd3 \u0dc0\u0dd3 \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc0\u0dda\u0dc1\u0db4\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb \u0dc4\u0dd2\u0d9f \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The train is overcrowded and tickets are running out",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Station officials say that with the increase in demand for trains, train tickets are running out and due to this situation, the issue of regular tickets in many stations will be a crisis.",
        "Station masters say that a problem is arising due to the running out of ordinary tickets at railway stations such as Colombo Fort, Maradana, Gampaha, Wayangoda and Ragama, as well as many sub-stations, and the railway department will have to bear huge costs in the future to import paper for printing ordinary tickets.",
        "Station officials who say that if the system of re-using used tickets is re-established, the cost of printing new tickets can be reduced to some extent and the railway authorities are not paying attention to the shortage of tickets.",
        "The railway station officials state that the tickets have been stopped through the government printing press and the printing equipment has been brought to the printing office at the railway headquarters and due to the failure to assign trained workers as well as enough workers for the office work, the work has slowed down."
      ],
